  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0bae\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bc8 \u0ba8\u0bc7\u0bbe\u0baf\u0bcd \u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bb0\u0bb5 \u0bb5\u0bbe\u0baf\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0ba4\u0bc1 : \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bae \u0b9c\u0bc0\u0bb5\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb0",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Monkey measles is likely to spread in Sri Lanka: Professor Chandima Jeevantara",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "Monkey measles has been identified in the United States and Europe without any international transport links.",
        "This is why the World Health Organization has declared an international public health emergency.",
        "As Monkey Measles is a viral disease, there is a risk that it can spread in Sri Lanka at any time, said Director of the Department of Immunology and Allergy, Sri Jayawardenapura University, Professor Chandima Jeevantara.",
        "He stated this while clarifying about monkey measles while the World Health Organization has declared an international public health emergency.",
        "Although monkey measles virus disease was initially identified only in South African countries, it has now been identified in the United States and European countries as well.",
        "Initially, the disease was found to be spread through international transport links. However, it is now recognized in cases where there are no international traffics.",
        "This is why the World Health Organization has declared an international public health emergency.",
        "In European countries, men are more affected by this disease. Most of them are identified as homosexuals.",
        "However, it has not been confirmed so far that the disease spreads through such sexual contact.",
        "Rather, it is confirmed that it is spread through close contact and breathing with people who are already infected. Monkey measles can be spread not only from humans but also from animals.",
        "The symptoms are initially fever and then rashes on the body skin. These are easily recognizable symptoms.",
        "The disease is transmitted through two main mutations. The mutations cause a 10 percent fatality rate.",
        "These are PCR. Can be identified through testing. The same facilities are available in other research institutes including Sri Jayawardenepura University.",
        "Compared to the covid virus, the monkey measles virus is 50 years old. However, it spreads at a slower rate than the covid infection.",
        "Medicines for this have already been discovered. The vaccine used for smallpox is 85 percent effective against monkey measles.",
        "Due to the increased spread of monkey measles in European countries, the World Health Organization has declared a public health emergency to encourage other countries to take precautionary measures.",
        "The disease has not been identified in Sri Lanka so far. However, since it is a viral disease, there is always a risk of transmission. He said that this can be avoided by wearing a face shield and avoiding close contact with those who are showing symptoms."
      ],
